text: Hua Yu Tseng (born 6 October 1986) is a Taiwanese volleyball player. She played for the Chinese Taipei women's national volleyball team. She played at the 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship and 2006 Asian Games. She played for National Taiwan Normal University's women's volleyball team. == References == Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Taiwanese volleyball players
